==Oh My Darling Clementine== ;1.) :In a{{crd|C}}cavern, in a canyon, - Excavating for a{{crd|G}}mine :Dwelt a{{crd|G7}}miner forty{{crd|C}}niner, - And his{{crd|G}}daughter Clemen-{{crd|C}}tine
;Chorus ::Oh my{{crd|C}}darling, oh my darling, - Oh my darling, Clemen-{{crd|G}}tine! ::Thou art{{crd|G7}}lost and gone for-{{crd|C}}ever - Dreadful{{crd|G}}sorry, Clemen-{{crd|C}}tine.
;2.) :Light she{{crd|C}}was and like a fairy, - And her shoes were number{{crd|G}}nine, :Herring{{crd|G7}}boxes, without{{crd|C}}topses, - Sandals{{crd|G}}were for Clemen-{{crd|C}}tine.
;3.) :Drove she{{crd|C}}ducklings to the water - Ev'ry morning just at{{crd|G}}nine, :Hit her{{crd|G7}}foot against a{{crd|C}}splinter, - Fell in-{{crd|G}}to the foaming{{crd|C}}brine.
;4.) :Ruby{{crd|C}}lips above the water, - Blowing bubbles, soft and{{crd|G}}fine, :But, alas, I{{crd|G7}}was no{{crd|C}}swimmer, - So I{{crd|G}}lost my Clemen-{{crd|C}}tine.
;5.) :How I{{crd|C}}missed her! How I missed her, - How I missed my Clemen-{{crd|G}}tine, :But I kissed her{{crd|G7}}little{{crd|C}}sister, - I for-{{crd|G}}got my Clemen-{{crd|C}}tine.
