<!-- PLEASE ADD CATEGORIES AND INTERWIKIS AT THE BOTTOM OF THIS PAGE -->

This template provides a quick way to mention an XML-style tag in a preformatted way. Mainly used in discussion/help pages.

=== Usage ===

*'''first parameter''' â€” ''(mandatory)''  the name of the HTML tag
*'''second parameter''' â€” what type of tag to display:
**<code>p</code> or <code>pair</code> â€“ ''(default)'' display a matched pair of open-and-close tags: {{tag|font|pair}}
**<code>o</code> or <code>open</code> â€“ display only the opening tag of an open-and-close pair: {{tag|span|open}}
**<code>c</code> or <code>close</code> â€“ display only the closing tag of an open-and-close pair: {{tag|span|close}}
**<code>s</code> or <code>single</code> â€“ display a single tag: {{tag|br|single}}
*'''content=''' â€” the text content of the tags
*'''params=''' â€” any parameters to be included in the opening tag

====Examples====

* <code><nowiki>{{tag|ref}}</nowiki></code> â†’ {{tag|ref}}
* <code><nowiki>{{tag|ref|content=hello}}</nowiki></code> â†’ {{tag|ref|content=hello}}
* <code><nowiki>{{tag|font|content=foo}}</nowiki></code> â†’ {{tag|font|content=foo}}
* <code><nowiki>{{tag|font|open}}</nowiki></code> â†’ {{tag|font|open}}
* <code><nowiki>{{tag|font|open|content=hello}}</nowiki></code> â†’ {{tag|font|open|content=hello}}
* <code><nowiki>{{tag|span|close|content=hello}}</nowiki></code> â†’ {{tag|span|close|content=hello}}
* <code><nowiki>{{tag|span|pair|content=hello}}</nowiki></code> â†’ {{tag|span|pair|content=hello}}
* <code><nowiki>{{tag|ref|open|params=group=note}}</nowiki></code> â†’ {{tag|ref|open|params=group=note}}
* <code><nowiki>{{tag|references|single}}</nowiki></code> â†’ {{tag|references|single}}
* <code><nowiki>{{tag|br|single}}</nowiki></code> â†’ {{tag|br|single}}

