This template can be used as a wrapper to simplify the inclusion of an image in a template, where users may use several different forms of syntax.

It is primarily of use in templates and should '''not''' be used in pages directly.

=== Usage ===

* <nowiki>{{Image | Example.svg | 20px}}</nowiki> â†’ {{Image | Example.svg | 20px}}
* <nowiki>{{Image | File:Example.svg | 20px}}</nowiki> â†’ {{Image | File:Example.svg | 20px}}
* <nowiki>{{Image | :File:Example.svg | 20px}}</nowiki> â†’ {{Image | :File:Example.svg | 20px}}
* <nowiki>{{Image | [[File:Example.svg|30px]] | 20px}}</nowiki> â†’ {{Image | [[File:Example.svg|30px]] | 20px}}

Note that additional parameters are (deliberately) ignored if full image syntax is passed in the first parameter. You can pass up to five parameters directly otherwise:
* <nowiki>{{Image | Example.svg | 20px | thumb | none | Foo}}</nowiki> â†’ {{Image | Example.svg | 20px | thumb | none | Foo}}

You can also pass arbitrary parameters accepted by the image syntax if you separate them with <nowiki>{{!}}</nowiki>. You may need to number them explicitly if they contain an equals sign "=":
* <nowiki>{{Image | Example.svg | 2= 20px{{!}}link=Main Page}}</nowiki> â†’ {{Image | Example.svg | 2= 20px{{!}}link=Main Page}}

=== See also ===
* {{tl|file title}}
* {{tl|linked}}
* {{tl|px}}
